SUBSTITUTE FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 4229
A bill to amend 2018 PA 435, entitled
"An act to create the office of school safety and prescribe its
powers and duties; and to provide for the powers and duties of
certain state entities,"
by amending section 3 (MCL 28.683).
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN ENACT:
1 Sec. 3. (1) The office of school safety shall do all of the
2 following:
3 (a) In conjunction with the department of education, create
4 model practices for school safety, including, but not limited to,
5 engaging with local law enforcement agencies to assess school
6 buildings for which emergency operation plans are being developed.
7 (b) Develop and offer training to school staff on school
LEP H00087'25 (H-1) va7826

2
1 safety. The office of school safety may contract with another party
2 to develop and offer the training required under this subdivision.
3 (c) In conjunction with the department of education, seek and
4 apply for federal funds relating to school safety and reducing
5 violence and disruption in schools, including, but not limited to,
6 federal funding for alternative schools or programs described in
7 section 1280a of the revised school code, 1976 PA 451, MCL
8 380.1280a.
9 (d) Create and administer a grant program to disburse
10 competitive school safety grants as appropriated by the legislature
11 to public schools, nonpublic schools, school districts, and
12 intermediate school districts to improve the safety and security of
13 school buildings, students, and staff.
14 (e) Compile quarterly reports of the tips received under
15 section 3 of the student safety act, 2013 PA 183, MCL 752.913, and
16 provide a copy of each report compiled under this subdivision to
17 the school safety and mental health commission established under
18 section 6 of the comprehensive school safety plan act, 2018 PA 548,
19 MCL 28.806.
20 (2) Subject to appropriation, the department of state police
21 shall provide the office of school safety with the staff and
22 resources necessary for the office to comply with this act.
23 Enacting section 1. This amendatory act does not take effect
24 unless House Bill No. 4258 of the 103rd Legislature is enacted into
25 law.
